ARTICLE IX ADDENDUM — AI TOOLS MARKETPLACE

  A9.1  CONFIDENTIALITY DESIGNATION

        This package is classified as INTERNAL CONFIDENTIAL within the
        MEDINA intelligence architecture. It contains the sovereign AI
        tools marketplace — a living ecosystem of 50+ enterprise tools,
        300+ extensions, worker tool bundles, and tool discovery
        intelligence that enables workers within the organism to find,
        deploy, and operate tools.

  A9.2  AUTHORIZED USE — INTERNAL DEVELOPMENT AND DEPLOYMENT

        (a) This package is authorized for internal use by the Author
            and by development teams operating under a valid MEDINA
            Internal Development Agreement (MIDA).

        (b) MIDA holders may integrate this marketplace into their
            MEDINA-powered deployments solely for internal tool
            discovery and worker enablement.

        (c) No portion of the marketplace may be exposed as a public
            service, public API, or public-facing tool store without
            a separate MEDINA Marketplace Distribution Agreement
            (MMDA) signed by the Author.

  A9.3  TOOL SUBMISSION

        (a) Third-party tools may be submitted to the marketplace
            only through the Author's sovereign submission process.

        (b) All submitted tools become subject to this license upon
            acceptance into the marketplace.

        (c) The Author retains absolute discretion over tool
            acceptance, rejection, and removal.

  A9.4  ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS (IN ADDITION TO ARTICLE III)

        (a) No competing marketplace, tool store, or tool discovery
            system may be derived from this package.

        (b) No tool metadata, categorization schema, or discovery
            algorithms may be extracted or replicated.

        (c) No marketplace analytics, usage data, or tool popularity
            metrics may be collected or shared externally.

  A9.5  TRADE SECRET DESIGNATION

        The marketplace architecture, discovery algorithms, tool
        categorization schema, and integration patterns constitute
        trade secrets under DTSA and TUTSA.

